Business Brief -- Energy Conversion Devices Inc.:
   Company Will Sell Shares
   Of OIS to Reduce Its Debt
The company, based in Troy, Mich., said proceeds from the
sale, after expenses, will be used to repay the remaining
$250,000 balance due to ANR Energy Conversion Co. Proceeds
will also be used to reduce Energy Conversion Devices'
obligations under the contingent promissory note by about
$2.6 million and for other corporate purposes equaling about
$780,000.
   After completion of this transaction, Energy Conversion
Devices will own 4,395,000 shares of OIS common stock, or
about 17% of the shares outstanding, which are pledged to
secure Energy Conversion Devices' obligations principally
under a contingent promissory note.